{
  "doc_id": "14657",
  "text": "Soft tissue grafts lead to a larger increase in bone tunnel diameter in comparison to bone-tendon-bone grafts [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . It has been proposed that graft fixation more closely to the joint line may reduce bone tunnel widening [CITATION_3] . Adversely, a larger extent of bone tunnel diameter was shown, when using bioabsorbable screws compared to an extracortical fixation at the tibial side [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
